    <content type="html"><![CDATA[<p><em>转自<a href="https://askubuntu.com/questions/31786/chrome-asks-for-password-to-unlock-keyring-on-startup#:~:text=You%20can%20start%20chrome%20with%20the%20command%20line,Chrome%2C%20this%20question%20should%20not%20be%20a%20duplicate.">StackOverFlow</a>:</em></p><blockquote><p>You can start chrome with the command line google-chrome –password-store&#x3D;basic so that it won’t ask use the gnome keyring. See: code.google.com&#x2F;p&#x2F;chromium&#x2F;wiki&#x2F;LinuxPasswordStorage Because there is a workaround that is specific to Chrome, this question should not be a duplicate.</p></blockquote><p>在启动命令中加入参数<code>--password-store=basic</code>即可解决。</p>]]></content>
    
    
      
      
